oai_dc:dc.dc:title: THE INFLUENCE OF SUBSURFACE CONDITIONS ON THE DESIGN OF FOUNDATIONS FOR WATERFRONT STRUCTURES IN THE GREAT LAKES AREA
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Peck, Ralph B.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Great Lakes
soil characteristics
foundation design
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: The purpose of this paper is to describe subsurface conditions beneath the principal waterfront areas in the Great Lakes region and to discuss certain foundation problems associated with waterfront structures in this locality.
oai_dc:dc.dc:source: Coastal Engineering Proceedings; No. 4 (1953): Proceedings of 4th Conference on Coastal Engineering, Chicago, Illinois, 1953.; 20
